      "content": "The idea that higher minimum wages stimulate local economies is a myth perpetuated by the progressive left. In reality, the economic benefits of higher minimum wages are largely theoretical and don't hold up to empirical evidence. The economic benefits of higher minimum wages are mostly felt by the workers themselves, not the local economy. The idea that higher minimum wages create a \"bottom-up\" economy is a feel-good narrative that ignores the harsh reality of how labor markets work.",
      "source": "target",
